  "prompt": "How much does an average subway franchise make per year?",
  "response": "The average Subway franchise can vary significantly in terms of annual revenue. As of recent reports, a typical Subway restaurant might generate anywhere from $300,000 to $500,000 in annual sales. However, individual performance can be influenced by factors such as location, local market conditions, management practices, and marketing efforts. Additionally, the net profit margin for franchises can vary, with many operators reporting profits ranging from 10% to 20% of total sales.\n\nFor the most accurate and current financial information, it is recommended to consult Subway's Franchise Disclosure Document (FDD) or speak directly with existing franchise owners.",
